           including as part of paid services, APIs, SaaS products,
           on-premise deployments, and shipped software;
       (c) Selling, licensing, or monetizing the neural-network models,
           weights, training pipelines, application code, or services
           that USE PromeTorch as a runtime dependency;
       (d) Building and selling AI-powered applications, websites, SDKs,
           mobile apps, or hardware products that embed PromeTorch as
           a library or runtime;
       (e) Consulting, integration services, custom training, fine-tuning,
           or deployment services, where PromeTorch is the underlying
           framework used to deliver the engagement;
       (f) Publishing derivative models, applications, or research results
           trained on PromeTorch, commercial or non-commercial.

   In plain terms: the framework is free and open — use it to build,
   train, and ship whatever you want, charge whatever you want for YOUR
   models and YOUR products. Only don't rebrand the framework itself and
   sell it as your own product.

